(474, 'Notes:: 1. **How did we connect?** 1. Raghu from PB 1. Raghu is a friend 1. He is being advised by Umang from CarDekho Group 1. Recently did the NCR visit circuit 1. **Pranil** 1. From Mumbai 1. South — suburbs — Ghatpokar — Powai now 1. GUJ middle class household 1. Dad is a trader of dry fruits & dates 1. Engineering — KJ Somaiya 1. MBA - GIM Goa 1. Citi banker for life 1. UHNI wealth mgt — ₹45 crore portfolio 1. Ratan tata family office client 1. Specialized domains across identity, fraud & risk 1. Karza 1. 0-1 journey as Product person 1. 8 member team at joining 1. 250 team at exit 1. Resp. w/ CTO to hire engineering staff of 150 1. Making 20L in revenue at entry 1. Making 85 crore in revenue at exit 1. Sold to Perfios for ₹650 crore 1. Built video KYC product + sandbox 1. Industry 1st product — reference check for onboarding new hires 1. Left a lot of money on table leaving prior to acquisition by Perfios 1. MetaMap 1. Moved to Mexico city for a bit 1. 15 member team (non-Indians; LATINO, EU etc) 1. $700K revenue in one year — self serve channel 1. Distressed sold to a global giant 1. Bureau.ID 1. Scaled x5 revenue on identity side 1. Head of Product role 1. He stumbled upon Tenacio 1. Waited for a long time — built for others; now for self 1. **Learning** 1. Perfios made Karza’s identity into a non-sexy industry 1. Identity biz is 85% GM — but lots of inbound competitors which brings the margin down 1. Karza growth rate is ~8% versus industry 20% 1. New players eating ...'),
(478, 'Meeting at the founder’s home 2024-08-29: Attendees: @Anonymous, @Aakash and @Rahul Mathur 1. Conversations with Mallika were very helpful - didn''t want to let her go after 45 minutes 1. Want to speak to Shashank from TWT but he hasn''t responded as yet to their message 1. Questions they asked - How is DeVC money invested? - who from DeVC would be leading the investment? - Is any board seat required? 1. General Qs they asked - Do we give a board seat? - what are drag rights? - should we be worried about exit clauses? 1. Have asked for one day to come back on the ₹2.5 crore + ₹0.5 crore allocation 1. Advice given by team - Move as many of the items to CS as possible - Push Fireside to close DD ASAP 1. Business right now - Doing ₹70L revenue - have a single fabric right now - going to China to speak to manufacturers to source one more new fabric 1. Other observations - Adith from Zepto is a friend, he has been giving them QC search data - CoFo has a sewing machine in her room which she uses to create samples - Founders aren''t surrounded by the right mentors, these are product marketers - Choksi''s family business on husband side is precision medical equipment which is sold to all types of hospitals and clinics - they have offered to help with MedMitra
Meeting at the founder’s office 2025-03-03: -'),
(479, 'Heads up note 2025-08-27T15:18:00.000+05:30 from @Rahul Mathur: Hi team, Sharing the heads-up note for our investment in [Tesora AI](https://tesora.ai/). It is an AI procurement analyst that streamlines the work of a sourcing team; starting with Hard Tech industries where qualified engineers earning $150K+ per annum are required to make calls / write emails to secure necessary components for complex systems. DeVC is investing $200K via the standard YC SAFE @ $20M Cap; this is a $3M round **Founders** 1. [Vivek R](https://www.linkedin.com/in/vivek-r-928871173/) 1. 2 YOE as PE investor at Sycamore Partners ($14b AUM) 1. 2 YOE @ McKinsey & Company 1. BRC from [Aditya Sukumar](https://www.linkedin.com/in/adithyasukumar?utm_source=share&utm_campaign=share_via&utm_content=profile&utm_medium=ios_app) (EM @ McKinsey) 1. *Top performer. Great technical skill set.* 1. *Definitely top decile compared to analysts and associates. * 1. *Would do whatever it took to get it done* 1. *Staying super late and being last one out was norm with him* 1. *Would you blindly back him: YES* 1. BA/MBA in Economics & Finance from UChicago; MBA was on full scholarship 1. [Federico G](https://www.linkedin.com/in/federico-reyes-gomez/) : 1. 3 YOE @ Kumo AI as founding engineer (fastest promotion) 1. *BRC from Viman Deb (Head of Product @ Kumo AI)* 1. *Fed is top 3 engineers in my 16 years career* 1. *Went on his own to use his extra time to be part of the solutions engineering team and going to customers. *...'),
(482, 'Notes:: **Views:** Yashi: Strong Maybe (should do more work with a 2PE) **Spiky: **0 **EF/FF: **FF **Founder Archetype: **6 **FMF: **7 **Thesis: **6 + found him very close to 0.5 spiky, is commercial and thoughtful + knows what he is building well – could answer 2-3 layers of questions ? working on building speciality textiles for various use cases across industries (more B2B than B2C) – should deep dive + has executed reasonably well within the limited time: got great customer logos on board, one core selling product and an R&D person from domain + Decent traction with high margins: 0.5 Cr MRR with 2.75 Cr in written orders, 16% CM3 average ? need to take all of this keeping in mind the history of building in textiles ? would like to diligence on the defensibility of the product and how real the pipeline is **Notes:** **Team** [Mayank Tibrewala](https://www.linkedin.com/in/mayank-tibrewala-9abab817/?originalSubdomain=in) - Background: - Born and raised in Mumbai in a Marwari family - Father was former CFO at WellSpin India, now runs his own CA/auditing firm - Mother is a homemaker - Has a younger sister who is a CA and IIM Lucknow graduate, working in private equity - Education: - Studied Aerospace Engineering at IIT Kharagpur - MBA from IIM Ahmedabad - Career: - Started at Arete Advisors (consulting, acquired by Bain) - Chief of Staff at Asaan Jobs (acquired by OLX) - Led global denims business at Fashinza ($15M ARR) (1 year) [**Akash Kalra**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/ak...'),
(483, 'Evaluation Plan + Key Questions to answer: 1. **What does the company do?** 1. 1. **Do we (DeVC/Z47) have a thesis on this space?** 1. 1. **What are the top 3 questions to diligence?** 1. 1. **Who has piped this company to us? What are their views?** 1. 1. **What do refs say about the founder?** 1. 1. **What''s the DeVC team views?** 1. 1. **What are the Collective signals?** 1. 1. **Why is this company likely to be special?** 1. 1. **Who can help? Experts / Venture Partners?** 1. 1. **Deal dynamics? Potential deal to do?** 1. ---
